  "gloss": "Every finite executed IEEE-754 float32 value, read as a real number, is exactly a dyadic rational (an integer divided by a power of two). This is the bridge that makes executed floating-point arithmetic exact mathematics rather than an approximation.\n\n**Cites** `TLT.Capacity.ieee32_toReal_mem_range_dyadicToReal` — the corpus theorem this result restates and discharges.\n\n**Original contribution.** The corpus lemma is a bare membership fact about a specific float encoding; the thesis-layer statement frames it as the foundational bridge that licenses treating an entire executed numerical system as exact real mathematics.\n",
